The paper deals with the Unique Games problem, which is a well-known problem in theoretical computer science and has connections to various subfields such as complexity theory, algorithms, and machine learning. The techniques used in the paper are based on statistical physics, which is a field that has been applied to various problems in computer science, including optimization, inference, and learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
